sql:
SELECT population, age_group, year
FROM population_data
WHERE population_id = (
    SELECT MAX(population_id)
    FROM population_data
);

SELECT population_id 
FROM population_data 
WHERE year = 2015 AND population = (SELECT MAX(population) FROM population_data WHERE year = 2015);

SELECT DISTINCT location_id
FROM population_data
WHERE age_group = '25-34' AND year = 2020 AND ethnicity = 'Asian';

SELECT SUM(population) AS total_child_population
FROM population_data
WHERE age_group = '0-14' AND year = 2023;

external_knowledge:
This query assumes that the 'survey' source type is the most reliable or relevant for forecasting; 
The 'city' location type is the primary geographic unit of interest for this forecast;
The forecast_value represents the projected population for each age group.
